description._content: Edinburgh was cold, yet bustling with shoppers. The German market had all types of food and drink for sale. Tanya tried the non-alcoholic mulled wine - it warmed her hands but tasted not as good as it looks :(
The big wheel at Princes Street gardens in Edinburgh Scotland.

A relatively short train ride from Lockerbie took us to Edinburgh and the Christmas Markets. It was heaving, there were crowds everywhere, Whilst it was freezing cold, it was a beautiful, crisp winter's day.

Has to be one of the most beautiful views in the world. 
Cranes are a pain in't erse though!!
3 exposures blended and edited.

Taken with the 18-55mm MKIII bought from e-bay for only £45. Took this lens for granted when I first bought it, but the image clarity it produces is superb!! Really happy with it!
